comment:
* Constants related to the LocationTimeZoneManager service that are used by shell commands and
 * tests.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: PRIMARY_PROVIDER_NAME
variables.comment: * The name of the primary location time zone provider, used for shell commands.

variables.name: SECONDARY_PROVIDER_NAME
variables.comment: * The name of the secondary location time zone provider, used for shell commands.

variables.name: SERVICE_NAME
variables.comment: * The name of the service for shell commands

variables.name: SHELL_COMMAND_START
variables.comment: * A shell command that starts the service (after stop).

variables.name: SHELL_COMMAND_STOP
variables.comment: * A shell command that stops the service.

variables.name: SHELL_COMMAND_CLEAR_RECORDED_PROVIDER_STATES
variables.comment: * A shell command that clears recorded provider state information during tests.

variables.name: SHELL_COMMAND_DUMP_STATE
variables.comment: * A shell command that tells the service to dump its current state.

variables.name: DUMP_STATE_OPTION_PROTO
variables.comment: * Option for {@link #SHELL_COMMAND_DUMP_STATE} that tells it to dump state as a binary proto.

variables.name: SHELL_COMMAND_START_WITH_TEST_PROVIDERS
variables.comment: A shell command that starts the location_time_zone_manager with named test providers.

variables.name: NULL_PACKAGE_NAME_TOKEN
variables.comment:
* The token that can be passed to {@link #SHELL_COMMAND_START_WITH_TEST_PROVIDERS} to indicate
     * there is no provider.
